# Waterfall Command Center — environment variables
#
# The app runs FULLY OFFLINE with zero config. These are only needed when you
# want AI skills to call a real language model instead of the local generators.
#
# Your endpoint should accept  POST { system?, prompt }  and return { text }.
# Keep your provider API key SERVER-SIDE (e.g. a Supabase Edge Function that
# calls Claude / another LLM). Never put a provider key directly in the browser.

# VITE_AI_API_URL=https://your-endpoint.example.com/generate
# VITE_AI_API_KEY=optional-bearer-token
